            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Hd1e108">Rubrica 12</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De timore Dei</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>¶ De timore dei. Rubrica. 12
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="53"/> <ref>IOb hystoria ca. 28.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e123">Timor
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>domini ipse est sapientia.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e129">
               <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>
               ¶ <ref>Moyses in deuteronomio. ca.
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e133">Timeas dominum deum tuum: et custodi
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>as mandata et precepta eius. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e142">
               <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
               ¶ <ref>Psalmista. 2 psalmus.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e146">Seruite domino in timore:
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>et exultate ei cum tremore. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e152"> /
       <ref>28. psalmus.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e154">Firma
        <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>mentum est dominus timentibus eum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e160"> /
       <ref>32. psalmus.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e162">Oculi domini super timentes eum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e168"> /
       <ref>84. psalmus.<ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e170">Pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="62" break="no"/>pe timentes deum salutare ipsius. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e176"> /
       <ref>102 psalmus.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e178">Minsericordia domini ab eterno: et vsque in eter
        <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>num super timentes eum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e186"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e188"> 110 psalmus. Initium sapien
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>tie timor domini. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e195"> /
       <ref>111 psalmus.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e197">Beatus vir qui ti
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>met dominum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e203"> /
      > <ref>148 psalmus.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e205"Beati omnes qui timens
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>dominum: qui ambulant in viis eius. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e211"> /
       <ref>165.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e213">Uo
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>luntatem timentium se faciet et depcationem eorum
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>exaudiet et saluos faciet eos. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e221"> /
       <ref>167 psalmus.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e223">Be
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>neplacitum est domino super timentes eum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e229">
               <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>
               ¶ <ref>Salomon in prouerb. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e233">Time deum et re
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>cede a malo. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e239"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e241"> Timor domini odit malum: arro
        <lb ed="#V" n="73" break="no"/>gantiam et superbiam et viam prauam: et os bilingue
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>detestatur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e250"> /
       <ref>15. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e252">Timor domini disciplia sapiente </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e256">
               <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>
               <ref>/ 16. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e260">Timore domini decliat a malo. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e264"> /
      <ref>.c. 24</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e266">Time dominum fili mi et regem. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e272"> /
       <ref>Idem in ecclesia
        <lb ed="#V" n="77" break="no"/>stico. cap. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e274">Qui timet dominum nihil negligit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e280">
               <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>
                <ref>/ 12. c. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e284">Deum time et mandatum eius obser
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>ua: h oc est enim omnis homo. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e290">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>
               ¶ <ref>Tobie hysto. cap. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e294">Multa bona habebi
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>mus si timuerimus deum: et recesserimus ab
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>omni peccato et fecerimus bene. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e303"> /
       <ref>Socrates in exhor
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>tationibus. c. 2. circa princi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e305">Deum quidem verere. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e311">
               <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>
               ¶ <ref>Iesus filius sirach in eccle. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e315">Timor domini
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>gloria et gloratio et letitia et corona exultationis.
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>Timor domini delectabit cor: et dabit letitiam es
        <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>gaudium et longitudinem dierum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e325"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e327"> Timenti dominm
        <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>bene erit in extremis: et in die defunctionis suc
        <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>benedicetur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e335"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e337"> Timor domini scientie religiosi
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>tas: custodiet et iustificabit cor. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e343"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e345"> Timer <!--32.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="5-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>deum bene erit: et in diebus consummationis illius
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>b enedicetur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e359"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e361"> Corona sapientie timor domini re
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>plens pacem et saluti fructum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e368"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e370"> Timor domini expel
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>lit peccatum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e376"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e378"> Qui timet dominum: honorat paren
        <lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>tes et quisi dominis fuiet is qui se genuerunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e384"> /
       <ref>7.
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e386">In tota anima tua time deum: et sacerdotes il
        <lb ed="#V" n="7" break="no"/>lius sacrifica. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e394"> /
       <ref>33. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e396">Timenti deum non occur
        <lb ed="#V" n="8" break="no"/>rent mala: sed in tentatione illum deus confuat: et
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>liberat a malis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e404"> /
       <ref>25 ca.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e406">Timor dei initium
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>dilectionis eius. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e412">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>
               ¶ <ref>Tucas in euange. c. 21.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e416">Timete eum qui post
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>quam occiderit habet ptantem mittere in gehenam </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e423">
               <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>
              ¶ <ref>Petrus apostolus epistola. i.</ref>  <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e427">Deum timete. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e431">
               <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>
               ¶ <ref>Augustinus in epigramatibus prospi. c. 71</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e435">Deus sic timendus est vt ab ipo fugiatur ad ipsum </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-d1e441">
               <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>
               ¶ <ref>Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 9. ca. 25.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de3258-Qd1e445">Semper bene
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>geritur si celestis metus humanis moribus ap
        <lb ed="#V" n="18" break="no"/>ponitur: hinc etenim virtutum omnium sumitu
        <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>agnitio hinc sapientia veritatis sapore conditur </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
